    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nlibvterm is missing some features and moving too slowly.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEvaluate if libghostty ~~or libvaxis~~ can replace libvterm.\n\n- full support (including scrollback) for reflow. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30117\n\nlibvaxis is more like a \"TUI sdk\" for building TUI apps. It could perhaps replace parts of `tui.c`, and [hopefully unibilium](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31989). Although libvaxis doesn't read terminfo, we may not need that anyway.",
